Package: pca
Type: Package
Title: Principal Components Analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Abby Mauger
Maintainer: Abby Mauger <asmauger@umich.edu>
Description: Computes principal components from a data matrix and provides two plotting functions.
    pca() carries out a principal component analysis using singular value decomposition and returns the eigenvectors, standard deviations of the PCs, and rotated data.
    elbowplot() creates an elbow/scree plot to visualize the percent variance explained by each PC.
    scoreplot() creates a PC score plot to visualize the rotated data.
